																		Keep Portland Weird
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183619" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1484764364 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Jan 2017 18:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2729149">
									

<p>Now that Three Portlands has its own tag, I figured it was time it got its own hub page. Anything tagged with <em>three-portlands</em> will automatically be listed on this page (with tales tagged with <em>unusual-incidents-unit</em> getting listed under Operations).</p>
<p>This page was originally written over 2 months ago, to serve as the eventual hub page for a UIU/Three Portlands series. Since I'm continuing to procrastinate on that particular series, and with the recent addition of the <em>three-portlands</em> tag, I figure this could be repurposed into a general hub for Three Portlands, written as an in-universe UIU dossier<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-997534-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-997534-1')">1</a></sup>.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Beyond a handful of establishing details<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-997534-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-997534-2')">2</a></sup>, there is no real style guide or set of rules for writing about Three Portlands. It's not a canon, or a group of interest, or even a character, and so there is no fixed tone or characterization to follow. It's a location, and how you use that location is entirely up to you.</span> See post lower down in this thread for updated info.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-997534-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-997534-1')">1</a>. Not unlike the Secure Facilities Dossiers that directly motivated me to write this piece in the first place.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-997534-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-997534-2')">2</a>. I.e. the entrances being in Portland, OR; Portland, ME; and the Isle of Portland; the city serving as a hub of anomalous activity; the lack of Foundation intervention</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
