								<div class="title" id="post-title-3640739">
																		Further Thoughts
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183619" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1511771385 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Nov 2017 08:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3640739">
									

<p>Three Portlands worldbuilding came up in the Third Law chat, and I figured I'd drop it here. You're free to take it or leave it if you're writing about Three Portlands, but I figured it might prove useful, especially for people working with the &quot;mainstream&quot; version of 3Ports. The transcripts have been lightly edited for spoilers of upcoming Third Law tales.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Some&nbsp;thoughts&nbsp;on&nbsp;geography</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Or&nbsp;lack&nbsp;thereof</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>&lt;TyGently&gt; worldbuilding thought: all the buildings in three portlands are very slowly moving away from the center of town<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; creating new space for building near the center and in the gaps formed between buildings<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; as they near the edge of town they get abandoned, eventually shuffle beyond the habitable border of three portlands, and in the long long term go past the boundary of the dimension and get obliterated<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; huh<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; this explains how three portlands seems to extend beyond its invisible walls and also explains how places like the abandoned school on the outskirts in austringers can exist<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; and city hall would naturally exist at the center<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; there are probably other dimensional landmarks too<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; like the Shadow of the Portland Observatory<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; yeah<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; the timescales are very slow, for obvious reasons<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; and it would fit with what I said in Analog Kid about the geography in three ports being fluid<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; &quot;especially near the peripherary&quot;<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; maybe two decades for something built on the edge of the center to reach the boundary<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; I was thinking more like 3 to 5<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; that could work too<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; since, like, the silver hand workshop opens in 1999, is abandoned in 2004, reopens in 2014, and is still operating in 2024<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; and that's already 2 decades<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; I'd imagine those thaumically or financially gifted enough could have their homes moved to habitable spots every once in a while<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; maybe the rate of movement is slower in different parts of the city<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; anchors like the Shadow of the PO slow it down for stuff in the vicinity, for example<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; a thought I had a while ago involved the impassable border being basically something imposed by the mayor rather than something inherent<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; more of a safety thing<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; makes sense<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; ooooh<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; that gives me fun ideas for UIU<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; getting permission from the mayor to go into the far periphery<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; to look for Clues<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; that would actually be super cool<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; abandoned portlands buildings, maybe some starting to fade into unreality<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; yes<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; what are you planning to do for the mayor<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; because I still like the idea of the mayor's office being a sort of black box</p>
<p>[Some spoileriffic discussion about the Mayor]</p>
<p>&lt;GreenWolf&gt; oh!<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; other thing that would be anchored against the outward movement<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; ICSUT campus<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; they'd definitely have the raw power to anchor their stuff<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; the campus is mounted on thousands of tiny caterpillar legs<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; pfft<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; alternately everything else just flows around it like a boulder in the middle of a river<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; that's what I was thinking<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; god, the street layout must be /amazing/<br />
&lt;GreenWolf&gt; this is also probably why they don't have heavy motor vehicles<br />
&lt;TyGently&gt; it helps that as the buildings spread outwards space appears between them, so there's all sorts of unconventional footpaths</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

