																		Major Hub Overhaul
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183619" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1550366557 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Feb 2019 01:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4155920">
									

<p>There's been a lot of demand in recent months for more details/clarification on many of the inner workings of Three Portlands, so after a lot of discussion with the other major 3Ports contributors (Conwell, TyGently, Taffeta, ch00bakka), I've gone ahead and pushed this massive, 6000+ word update to the hub that now provides extensive worldbuilding information about the city. A lot of this is stuff that we had already agreed upon for the city but had only referenced in tales, or had never formally codified, although there's a bit of new info here as well.</p>
<p>I know I initially said that there wasn't really a fixed tone or characterization for Three Ports, but the demands of a shared location require a relatively consistent depiction, even if individual details might vary depending on particular canon. What's presented here is meant to establish a &quot;core canon&quot; for the city &#8212; individual authors are, of course, free to diverge from this as much as they like, but this page is meant to represent what the essential essence of Three Portlands is. Part of the intent of the &quot;Notable Cases&quot; section is to showcase tales that present this essential Portlands in an effective manner, before listing every page tagged with <em>three-portlands</em>.</p>
<p>Big thanks to TyGently, Conwell, Taffeta, ch00bakka, ARD, NineVolt, and tawny for critique and feedback on this while it was going through drafting. TyGently and Conwell deserve special shoutouts for the extensive amount of worldbuilding they've helped contribute to Three Portlands over the past two years.</p>
<p>Remember, Keep Portland Weird.</p>

							</div>

								
					
