			<div class="content" id="post-content-2729179">
									

<p>Hey hey, trade in the small wigs for a the big wigs, Three Portlands has a hub.</p>
<p>The info presented here really does provide good context for what Three Portlands is, and what the UIU relationship is with the numerous people and anomalous beings that live there. Plenty of worldbuilding to be had.</p>
<p>My personal favorite line, though, would be:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The counter-cultural movement of the 60s and 70s was reflected in Three Portlands, giving rise to a vibrant anart scene. The growth of the city's anart community was further fueled by Foundation efforts to expel anartists from urban areas in North America and Europe, forcing them into pocket dimensions like Three Portlands and Backdoor Soho.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It would be interesting to read a tale about the forced migration of practitioners of the anomalous to these pocket dimensions. I'd be curious what name the anartists and others gave to the movement.</p>
<p>Either way. +1</p>

